ts useful guidelines that will help them to ensure that all aspects of effective HIV prevention programmes are occurring in their location. http://www.burnet.internationalhealth.edu.au/ freestyler/gui/files/toolkit_part1.pdf United Nations Development Program. From Challenges to Opportunities: responses to trafficking and HIV/AIDS in South Asia. 2003 This publication includes brief analyses of the work of several organizations whose work focuses on reducing the vulnerability of women in the context of trafficking and provides a useful overview of key domains and approaches for intervention. http://www.undprcc.lk/Our_Work/HIV_and_ Development.asp 151 CHAPTER 04 | Key Topics REFEREnCEs Azad, Nandini, \u201cTrafficked Female Labor: Coping Mechanisms for Poor Households.\u201d Available at www.hawaii.edu/global/projects_activities/Traf- ficking/_Azad.do Coalition Against Trafficking in Women (CATW). \u201cFactbook: Southeast Asia and Pacific.\u201d Available at: http://www.catwinternational.org/factbook/ Asia_Pacific.php Hong, K.T., Van Anh, N.T & Ogden, J. (2004). \u201cBecause this is the disease of the century\u201d Un- derstanding HIV and AIDS-related Stigma and Discrimination. Washington, D.C.: International Center for Research on Women. International Center for Research on Women. (2005). Stigma and Violence Reduction Inter- ventions in Andhra Pradesh, India: emerging themes from community-based intervention research on stigma, HIV/AIDS and intimate part- ner violence. Research Update. Washington D.C. Kilmarx, P.H., Limpakarnjanarat, K., Mastro, T.D., Saisorn, S., Kaewkungwal, J., Korattana, S., Uthaivoravit, W., Young, N.L., Weniger, B.G., & St Louis, M.E. (1998). HIV-1 seroconversion in a pro- spective study of female sex workers in north- ern Thailand: continued high incidence among brothel-based women. AIDS, 12(14), 1889-98. Meeting the Challenge. AVAHAN India AIDS Initiative. Available at: http://www.gatesfoun- dation.org/GlobalHealth/Pri_Diseases/HIVAIDS/ HIV